2. Theoretical Framework

2.1 Narrative Superposition Model (NSM)

Narrative Superposition is defined as:

A corporate communication state in which a technology is simultaneously described as Early, Experimental, Dangerous, Revolutionary, Inevitable, and Available Now With Team Pricing.

The user is therefore required to operate in Quantum Marketing Reality (QMR), where product capability exists in a probabilistic state until opened in a browser.

2.2 The Expectation–Reality Compression Cycle (ERCC)

The Institute has identified a repeating psychological cycle:

Stage	Corporate Message	User Experience
1	“This changes everything.”	User opens app
2	“This is AGI-adjacent.”	User writes email
3	“This will transform work.”	User summarizes PDF
4	“This is the future of humanity.”	User asks for Excel formula
5	“This is a new species of intelligence.”	User fixes bullet points
6	“This is just the beginning.”	User closes laptop

This loop repeats indefinitely and is known as the Productivity Groundhog Day Protocol (PGDP).

