6. Key Findings

The Institute’s primary finding is the Sanity Preservation Paradox (SPP):

The more you use the tools for real work, the less insane the industry sounds.

A secondary finding is the Inverse Announcement Law (IAL):

The louder the announcement, the more likely the feature is a sidebar.

⸻

7. Concluding Statement

After extensive research, the Institute concludes that users are not trapped in Narrative Superposition and that messaging is appropriately calibrated to product capability. Reports of cognitive dissonance are likely due to users misunderstanding that drafting emails faster, summarizing PDFs, generating code, automating spreadsheets, writing reports, creating presentations, analyzing data, and building software are all minor features and not at all world-changing.

The Institute therefore recommends that users remain calm, continue working, and prepare for the next announcement that will permanently change everything again next Tuesday.

